On December 22, 2021, the President signed into law the Capitol Police Emergency Assistance Act of 2021, also known as S. 3377. This law grants the Chief of the Capitol Police the authority to seek assistance from federal agencies during emergencies. The President expressed gratitude to Senators Klobuchar, Blunt, King, Wicker, Feinstein, Capito, Merkley, Padilla, and Warner for their leadership in this matter.